    <div id="main"><h2>06/10/2024</h2>
      <div id="entry-92430504">
        <div>
          <h3>I meditated while feeling a drop in the heart (void-bliss-union)</h3>
        </div>
      </div>I meditated during the day. I meditated with my legs stretched out in a surf chair because I fall asleep easily in the sleeping position. I let my mind dissolve into emptiness without thinking. When I do this, I feel a drop in my heart and feel bliss. This is the Tibetan Esoteric Buddhist method of practicing void-bliss-union. Then I continue meditating in the sleeping posture.
</p>Then I did the astral projection in the room. In order to stabilize the astral body, I didn't go out of the room, but I kept moving around in circles in the room. While doing this, I kept chanting mantras, clasping my hands, and floating. After a long time, sexual desire arose. Then the astral projection ended.
</p>Before, when I meditated during the day without thinking, I could often do astral projection, but the astral body was usually unstable. This time I meditated while also feeling drops and bliss in my heart, which might have been a factor in astral projection for a long time.
